<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="598" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/1291: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-27T18:00:00-04:00">February 27, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1282. “For Harriman from Stettinius. Reference your 1391,<note n="65" xml:id="d598fn65">Not printed.</note> full U.S. commitment for
                                duraluminum has already been met. Nevertheless, more duraluminum
                                sheets have been and will continue to be supplied to meet Soviet
                                requests and in pro rata satisfaction of aluminum ingot commitment.
                                The increase we referred to is 1,300 tons aluminum ingots and 2,200
                                tons duraluminum sheets over and above total U.S. commitment for
                                both duraluminum and aluminum.”</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>